
Overview of noun onslaught

The noun onslaught has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) onslaught -- (a sudden and severe onset of trouble)
2. (2) attack, onslaught, onset, onrush -- ((military) an offensive against an enemy (using weapons); "the attack began at dawn")
3. barrage, bombardment, outpouring, onslaught -- (the rapid and continuous delivery of linguistic communication (spoken or written); "a barrage of questions"; "a bombardment of mail complaining about his mistake")
